The Duke of Edinburgh's memorial will be Andrew's first public engagement since his father's funeral last year. Andrew stepped down from royal duties in November 2019 and has been keeping a low profile ever since. In January, the Queen stripped Andrew of his military and HRH titles, following the news that the prince was to face a civil sexual abuse trial in the US. However, Andrew reached an out-of-court settlement in principle with his accuser in February. The settlement was not an admission of guilt, and Andrew has vehemently denied all claims against him. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES.... 